<TITLE> Rice says Afghanistan policy review nearly complete </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 COPENHAGEN, Fri Dec 5, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice on Friday said the Bush administration's review of its policy for Afghanistan is almost complete. "It's being reviewed by the principals of the National Security Council and it is going to be discussed with our friends," said Rice, who was in Copenhagen as part of a European tour to say farewell to other top diplomats before the Bush administration's term ends on Jan. 20, 2009. "I expect that some elements of it will be made public in some way. We haven't determined what can and what cannot," she said. The Bush administration, the US military's Joint Staff and the US Central Command under US Army Gen. David Petraeus are all undertaking reviews of US policy toward Afghanistan
